The following items are suggested as helpful, pick and choose what works for you and your teen:
A desk tidy: a desk tidy helps to keep stationary organized and a desk clear and neat. You can also get desk tidies for papers so homework can be put into the tidy and kept safe. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-9.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-9.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-9.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A bin: A small bin with a lid, to stop odors, can be a life saver. Tell your teenager to put all their rubbish into the bin and you could even give them a small reward for filling the bin with their rubbish. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2e/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-10.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-10.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2e/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-10.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-10.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A shoe rack: This can be hidden in the wardrobe, but this can encourage teenagers to keep their shoes together and organized so if they need a pair of shoes they are easy to find. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-11.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-11.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-11.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-11.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A wash basket: Tell your teenager to put all their washing into the washing basket and like the bin you could give them a small reward for filling the basket. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-12.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-12.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-12.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-12.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Noticeboard: This helps in organizing your teenager and they can write down any assignments or important dates etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-13.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-13.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-13.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-13.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bag hanger: All bags will have a place and coats can even be hung up here. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-14.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-14.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-14.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-14.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

A clear cupboard: Tell your teenager to store all their games or other possessions in here to keep the room clean. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-15.jpg/v4-460px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-15.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-15.jpg/v4-760px-Keep-a-Teenager%27s-Bedroom-Clean-Step-15.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
